---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const updated = 'June 1, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — PaycheckCalc"
  description="PaycheckCalc privacy policy. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-body">
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="intro">
        Your privacy matters to us. This Privacy Policy explains how PaycheckCalc ("we", "us", "our")
        collects, uses, and protects information when you visit <strong>paycheck-calc.vercel.app</strong>
        (the "Site").
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>Information You Enter in the Calculator</h3>
      <p>
        All calculations are performed entirely in your browser. The income, state, filing status,
        and dependent information you enter into the calculator is <strong>never sent to our servers</strong>
        and is not stored or logged in any way.
      </p>
      <h3>Automatically Collected Information</h3>
      <p>
        Like most websites, we may automatically receive standard technical information when you visit,
        including your browser type, referring URL, pages viewed, and time spent on pages. This data is
        collected in aggregate and cannot be used to identify you personally.
      </p>
      <h3>Cookies</h3>
      <p>
        We use minimal cookies for site analytics (e.g., page views) and to remember your preferences
        (such as your most recently selected state). We do not use advertising cookies or cross-site
        tracking cookies.
      </p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To serve and improve the Site</li>
        <li>To analyze usage patterns and fix bugs</li>
        <li>To respond to contact form submissions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties.</p>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        We may use third-party analytics services (such as Google Analytics or Plausible Analytics)
        to understand how visitors use our Site. These services may collect anonymized usage data
        subject to their own privacy policies.
      </p>
      <p>
        This Site is hosted on <strong>Vercel</strong>. Vercel may collect standard server logs.
        See <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vercel's Privacy Policy</a>
        for details.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        Since financial data entered in the calculator never leaves your browser, there is no risk
        of that data being intercepted or stored by us. We use HTTPS to encrypt all traffic between
        your browser and our servers.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our Site is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal
        information from children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal
        information we hold about you. To exercise these rights, contact us at hello@paycheck-calc.com.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page
        with an updated "Last updated" date. Continued use of the Site after changes constitutes
        acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this Privacy Policy? Contact us at <a href="/contact">our contact page</a>
        or email hello@paycheck-calc.com.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a56db 0%, #1447c0 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 48px 20px 44px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .page-hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .page-hero p  { opacity: .78; font-size: 0.9rem; }

  .page-body { padding-top: 48px; padding-bottom: 64px; }
  .intro { font-size: 1rem; color: #374151; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 32px; padding: 18px 20px; background: #f9fafb; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #1a56db; }

  .prose h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 32px 0 10px; color: #111827; }
  .prose h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 18px 0 8px; color: #374151; }
  .prose p  { color: #374151; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 14px; font-size: 0.925rem; }
  .prose ul { margin: 0 0 14px 24px; }
  .prose li { color: #374151; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 4px; font-size: 0.925rem; }
  .prose strong { color: #111827; }
  .prose a { color: #1a56db; }
</style>
